<topic id='element_earliest_clinically_appropriate_date.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: EARLIEST CLINICALLY APPROPRIATE DATE - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_earliest_clinically_appropriate_date">EARLIEST CLINICALLY APPROPRIATE DATE</xref>
 is the earliest date that it was clinically appropriate for an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity">ACTIVITY</xref>
 to take place.        </p>
      <p>
For the 
              <xref outputclass="dataSet" keyref="dataset_radiotherapy_data_set">Radiotherapy Data Set</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_earliest_clinically_appropriate_date">EARLIEST CLINICALLY APPROPRIATE DATE</xref>
 is the:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
first date that the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 would have been clinically fit to start 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_radiotherapy">Radiotherapy</xref>
 and                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
same as the 
                                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_decision_to_treat_date">DECISION TO TREAT DATE</xref>
 unless there was an elective delay, i.e. a clinical reason, such as the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 was not fit.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
For the 
              <xref outputclass="dataSet" keyref="dataset_community_services_data_set">Community Services Data Set</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="dataSet" keyref="dataset_mental_health_services_data_set">Mental Health Services Data Set</xref>
 and 
              <xref href="https://v3.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/navigation/commissioning_data_sets_menu.html"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Commissioning Data Sets</xref>
 (version 6-2 onwards), the 
              <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_earliest_clinically_appropriate_date">EARLIEST CLINICALLY APPROPRIATE DATE</xref>
 may be used locally to inform waiting time calculations. It can be used to account for periods of time where it is not appropriate to treat the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 for clinical reasons, for example:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
where the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 has been admitted to hospital for an unrelated condition and the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICE</xref>
 cannot commence planned treatment until the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 has been discharged                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
where the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is frail and cannot be treated until their condition improves, but it is not appropriate to discharge the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 from the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICE</xref>.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
  </div>
</body>
